facebook

Class FacebookAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • socialmedia.SocialMediaBase<FacebookUser,FacebookPost>
      • facebook.FacebookAPI
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SocialMediaAPI<FacebookUser,FacebookPost>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FacebookAPIImpl

    public abstract class FacebookAPI
extends SocialMediaBase<FacebookUser,FacebookPost>
    Handles API calls for Facebook. Where functions take an id of a specific user, an id of 'me' will translate to the current user. getUser("me") will as such get all information about the current user.

      • getUser

        public abstract FacebookUser getUser(java.lang.String id)
        Gets a Facebook user, filling a user object with the available information. As users have a large degree of flexibility regarding what's visible, some data may be null, even if the user has set the information. If id is 'me', will retrieve the current user
        Parameters:
        id - Site-wide id of the user
        Returns:
        A FacebookUser
